### Description

Whats the advantage of [fullPage.js](https://github.com/alvarotrigo/fullPage.js) vs plain `CSS`

```css
.fullpage {
    display: flex;
    overflow: auto;

    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;

    flex: none;
    flex-flow: column nowrap;
    scroll-snap-type: y mandatory;
}

.fullpage > div {
    scroll-snap-align: center;
    flex: none;
    height: 100%;
}
```

example-[link](https://fullpagecss.netlify.app/)

I'm trying to change the direction every time the page isn't an even number, however this causes some bugs with the pages.
The following code should reproduce, place it in one of the callbacks like `afterLoad`
```
        if (index % 2 == 0) {
            $("#pagepiling").pagepiling().direction="vertical"
        } else {
            $("#pagepiling").pagepiling().direction="horizontal"
        }
```

In short, it works for like 3 pages, then the pages duplicate, and following that it completely bugs out, and horizontal scroll stops working.

I'm trying to change the direction every time the page isn't an even number, however this causes some bugs with the pages.
The following code should reproduce, place it in one of the callbacks like `afterLoad`
```
        if (index % 2 == 0) {
            $("#pagepiling").pagepiling().direction="vertical"
        } else {
            $("#pagepiling").pagepiling().direction="horizontal"
        }
```

In short, it works for like 3 pages, then the pages duplicate, and following that it completely bugs out, and horizontal scroll stops working.

I'm trying to change the direction every time the page isn't an even number, however this causes some bugs with the pages.
The following code should reproduce, place it in one of the callbacks like `afterLoad`
```
        if (index % 2 == 0) {
            $("#pagepiling").pagepiling().direction="vertical"
        } else {
            $("#pagepiling").pagepiling().direction="horizontal"
        }
```

In short, it works for like 3 pages, then the pages duplicate, and following that it completely bugs out, and horizontal scroll stops working.

comment.body:
Unfortunately, the direction can't be set after initialization.

You can only do it this way:

```js
 if (index % 2 == 0) {
    $('#pagepiling').pagepiling({ 
       direction: ' vertical'
    });
}
else {
    $('#pagepiling').pagepiling({ 
       direction: ' horizontal'
    });
}
```

